WEBVTT

1
00:00:26.360 --> 00:00:28.820
- He loves that old camera.
- Come on. Yang.

2
00:00:29.905 --> 00:00:31.823
[Yang] One second.

3
00:00:31.907 --> 00:00:34.660
- Don't forget to join us.
- I will.

4
00:00:35.869 --> 00:00:37.287
Look here for a second.

5
00:00:39.581 --> 00:00:41.667
What are you doing? Come on.

6
00:00:41.750 --> 00:00:43.085
Come on. <i>gege.</i>

7
00:00:49.007 --> 00:00:52.010
[soft piano music playing]

8
00:01:00.394 --> 00:01:03.730
[Jake] <i>Yellow Equinox.
Is that a new blend?</i>

9
00:01:03.814 --> 00:01:04.815
[woman] <i>I think so.</i>

10
00:01:04.898 --> 00:01:07.609
I'm sure I can make you something close
to it. You know what kind of tea leaves?

11
00:01:07.693 --> 00:01:09.695
Oh. no. No. no. It's not this kind of tea.

12
00:01:09.778 --> 00:01:11.655
I'm looking for your crystallized teas.

13
00:01:11.738 --> 00:01:15.409
Ah. Sorry. I-I don't carry tea crystals.

14
00:01:15.492 --> 00:01:18.704
How can you be a tea shop
and not carry tea crystals?

15
00:01:18.787 --> 00:01:19.997
[sighs] How frustrating.

16
00:01:20.080 --> 00:01:22.291
Why don't you let me make you
something that might be close?

17
00:01:22.374 --> 00:01:25.210
No. No. no. no. This is... I have to go.

18
00:01:26.461 --> 00:01:27.879
Thanks for coming in.

19
00:01:38.765 --> 00:01:41.935
- [Mika] <i>When's Daddy coming home?</i>
- [Kyra] <i>Soon.</i>

20
00:01:42.936 --> 00:01:45.772
He's always late.

21
00:01:46.773 --> 00:01:50.193
Well. I'm late sometimes. too.

22
00:01:50.277 --> 00:01:54.740
And. you know. I've got a busy
few weeks coming up. so...

23
00:01:54.823 --> 00:01:58.243
- I know. Yang will be here.
- So will Daddy.

24
00:01:59.244 --> 00:02:00.245
Mika.

25
00:02:02.122 --> 00:02:03.206
Mika?

26
00:02:04.499 --> 00:02:06.293
Don't be too hard on him.

27
00:02:06.376 --> 00:02:09.838
He told me there was a rush of customers
towards the end of the day.

28
00:02:09.921 --> 00:02:13.550
That's good news for Daddy.
He needed that.

29
00:02:27.564 --> 00:02:29.316
[Kyra] <i>I loved that meal.</i>

30
00:02:29.399 --> 00:02:31.443
Did you like the gochujang sauce?

31
00:02:31.526 --> 00:02:33.153
- [Jake] I did.
- I made it.

32
00:02:33.236 --> 00:02:34.738
[Jake] You mentioned that.

33
00:02:34.821 --> 00:02:36.406
It was her first time.

34
00:02:36.490 --> 00:02:41.078
So you put the ingredients in the bowl
and you mixed them all together?

35
00:02:42.245 --> 00:02:43.664
- Yeah.
- [Jake chuckles]

36
00:02:43.747 --> 00:02:44.831
It's good. huh?

37
00:02:46.375 --> 00:02:48.085
It was really wonderful. <i>mei mei.</i>

38
00:02:48.168 --> 00:02:49.544
Thank you.

39
00:02:49.628 --> 00:02:52.964
Next time. I'm gonna Juliet the carrots.

40
00:02:53.048 --> 00:02:54.633
Julienne.

41
00:02:54.716 --> 00:02:56.385
And no. you're not. [chuckles]

42
00:02:56.468 --> 00:02:58.470
[violin playing]

43
00:03:11.483 --> 00:03:13.276
Mika's growing up so fast.

44
00:03:13.360 --> 00:03:15.779
[muffled violin continues playing]

45
00:03:15.862 --> 00:03:18.448
She keeps asking why we're always busy.

46
00:03:20.742 --> 00:03:22.536
She understands.

47
00:03:22.619 --> 00:03:25.038
- And Yang is...
- No. she doesn't.

48
00:03:26.665 --> 00:03:28.417
[sighs]

49
00:03:28.500 --> 00:03:29.668
I feel like...

50
00:03:31.795 --> 00:03:33.046
I don't know. I...

51
00:03:36.341 --> 00:03:37.676
I don't want to regret.

52
00:03:37.759 --> 00:03:40.470
Um... Um. I'll make more time.

53
00:03:41.471 --> 00:03:44.474
I will. I promise.

54
00:03:45.934 --> 00:03:48.895
You know I'm not putting this
on you. right?

55
00:03:48.979 --> 00:03:50.731
Hmm. Sort of.

56
00:03:50.814 --> 00:03:52.816
- I'm not.
- I'm teasing.

57
00:03:55.068 --> 00:03:58.071
I just want us to be a team.

58
00:03:59.698 --> 00:04:00.782
A family.

59
00:04:00.866 --> 00:04:02.075
- [techno music playing]
♪ <i>-Starting</i> ♪

60
00:04:02.159 --> 00:04:03.910
♪ <i>Ignite</i> ♪

61
00:04:03.994 --> 00:04:05.203
♪ <i>Starting</i> ♪

62
00:04:05.287 --> 00:04:06.872
♪ <i>Reset</i> ♪

63
00:04:06.955 --> 00:04:08.165
♪ <i>Starting</i> ♪

64
00:04:08.248 --> 00:04:09.875
♪ <i>Ignite</i> ♪

65
00:04:09.958 --> 00:04:11.209
♪ <i>Starting</i> ♪

66
00:04:11.293 --> 00:04:12.878
♪ <i>Reset</i> ♪

67
00:04:12.961 --> 00:04:14.254
♪ <i>Starting</i> ♪

68
00:04:14.337 --> 00:04:15.881
♪ <i>Starting</i> ♪

69
00:04:15.964 --> 00:04:17.174
♪ <i>Starting</i> ♪

70
00:04:17.257 --> 00:04:18.800
♪ <i>Starting</i> ♪

71
00:04:25.307 --> 00:04:29.436
[Host. over speaker] <i>Welcome. families
of four. to our monthly dance-off.</i>

72
00:04:29.519 --> 00:04:33.148
<i>We have over 30.000 families
competing tonight.</i>

73
00:04:34.733 --> 00:04:36.985
<i>Are you ready?</i>

74
00:04:37.068 --> 00:04:38.945
[music tempo increases]

75
00:04:39.029 --> 00:04:40.447
<i>Stay in sync.</i>

76
00:04:43.074 --> 00:04:45.076
<i>Precision points added.</i>

77
00:04:50.874 --> 00:04:52.167
<i>Take flight.</i>

78
00:04:58.298 --> 00:04:59.716
<i>Ready for combat.</i>

79
00:05:03.261 --> 00:05:04.679
<i>Fight time.</i>

80
00:05:11.895 --> 00:05:13.730
<i>Level one complete.</i>

81
00:05:15.857 --> 00:05:18.568
<i>Three thousand families eliminated.</i>

82
00:05:19.778 --> 00:05:21.196
<i>Stay together.</i>

83
00:05:22.447 --> 00:05:23.406
<i>Steady.</i>

84
00:05:28.453 --> 00:05:30.080
<i>Sync bonus coming up.</i>

85
00:05:43.718 --> 00:05:45.595
<i>The hitchhiker.</i>

86
00:05:45.679 --> 00:05:46.680
<i>Go.</i>

87
00:05:51.601 --> 00:05:53.395
<i>Transition.</i>

88
00:05:53.478 --> 00:05:55.063
<i>Collect the TNT.</i>

89
00:06:00.443 --> 00:06:01.486
<i>Detonate.</i>

90
00:06:01.570 --> 00:06:02.696
[beeping]

91
00:06:07.534 --> 00:06:10.829
<i>Smile. It's time for family portrait.</i>

92
00:06:10.912 --> 00:06:12.289
[timer beeping]

93
00:06:12.372 --> 00:06:13.999
- [click]
<i>- Earthquake.</i>

94
00:06:17.752 --> 00:06:19.045
<i>Tornado time.</i>

95
00:06:23.425 --> 00:06:25.093
<i>Level two complete.</i>

96
00:06:26.761 --> 00:06:29.180
<i>Nine thousand families eliminated.</i>

97
00:06:31.433 --> 00:06:33.059
<i>Stamina round.</i>

98
00:06:36.313 --> 00:06:38.815
<i>Keep up.</i>

99
00:06:38.899 --> 00:06:40.275
<i>Stay in sync.</i>

100
00:06:42.777 --> 00:06:44.029
<i>- Terminated.</i>
- [music stops ]

101
00:06:44.112 --> 00:06:46.323
- [groans loudly]
- Babe! Babe!

102
00:06:46.406 --> 00:06:48.909
It wasn't me. It was... [panting]

103
00:06:48.992 --> 00:06:50.952
It wasn't me! Mika?

104
00:06:51.036 --> 00:06:52.662
Not me! It was Daddy!

105
00:06:52.746 --> 00:06:55.540
- Mm-hmm.
- That's the furthest we've ever gone.

106
00:06:55.624 --> 00:06:56.791
[laughs] That's true.

107
00:06:56.875 --> 00:06:58.919
- Yang. we're... we're out.
- [Mika laughing]

108
00:06:59.002 --> 00:07:00.420
Yang? Yang!

109
00:07:00.503 --> 00:07:01.630
- [Mika] <i>Yang!</i>
- [Jake] <i>Yang?</i>

110
00:07:20.440 --> 00:07:22.984
[Jake] It looks like we have three years
left on the warranty.

111
00:07:23.068 --> 00:07:25.362
- but they're not answering. so...
- [Kyra] Can't you just go there?

112
00:07:25.445 --> 00:07:27.989
[Jake] Yeah. I'm going to. but I don't
know if the store is even there anymore.

113
00:07:28.073 --> 00:07:29.699
I did a search.
I can't find them anywhere.

114
00:07:29.783 --> 00:07:30.992
Did you call Brothers & Sisters?

115
00:07:31.076 --> 00:07:32.535
We didn't buy from them directly. so...

116
00:07:32.619 --> 00:07:33.954
[Kyra] They won't honor the warranty?

117
00:07:34.037 --> 00:07:36.039
No. the warranty is with Second Siblings.

118
00:07:36.122 --> 00:07:37.332
[sighs softly]

119
00:07:39.542 --> 00:07:41.252
I told you we should've
just bought a new one.

120
00:07:41.336 --> 00:07:44.339
He was new. I mean. practically.

121
00:07:44.422 --> 00:07:45.674
He's refurbished.

122
00:07:45.757 --> 00:07:47.342
Certified refurbished.

123
00:07:47.425 --> 00:07:49.886
And he'd only been in use
for five days. Five days.

124
00:07:49.970 --> 00:07:52.263
- And we saved...
- But now he...

125
00:07:52.347 --> 00:07:54.724
Never mind. Let's just get him fixed.

126
00:07:54.808 --> 00:07:56.226
Yeah.

127
00:07:56.309 --> 00:07:57.602
You need to get Mika to school.

128
00:07:57.686 --> 00:07:59.688
Mika. come on. we need to go!

129
00:08:03.775 --> 00:08:04.859
Mika?

130
00:08:11.116 --> 00:08:13.368
- Mika?
- What happened to Yang?

131
00:08:14.411 --> 00:08:16.955
Oh. hi. Um...

132
00:08:18.164 --> 00:08:19.165
I don't know.

133
00:08:19.249 --> 00:08:21.376
He shut down last night.
He won't restart.

134
00:08:21.459 --> 00:08:23.169
- Has this happened before?
- No.

135
00:08:24.421 --> 00:08:27.007
- You got a technician?
- He's still under warranty.

136
00:08:27.090 --> 00:08:29.509
I wouldn't take him back
to Brothers & Sisters.

137
00:08:29.592 --> 00:08:32.470
They're just going to try to get you
to recycle him for a new model.

138
00:08:32.554 --> 00:08:34.055
You know why.

139
00:08:34.139 --> 00:08:35.557
I'm not taking him there.

140
00:08:35.640 --> 00:08:37.851
The warranty's with another store.

141
00:08:37.934 --> 00:08:40.186
You didn't buy him direct?

142
00:08:40.270 --> 00:08:43.732
No. No. uh. he's certified.

143
00:08:43.815 --> 00:08:45.233
I have to go and get Mika.

144
00:08:45.316 --> 00:08:46.735
Oh. Mika's still here?

145
00:08:46.818 --> 00:08:48.069
Did she see Yang all dead-eyed?

146
00:08:48.153 --> 00:08:49.779
- I bet it freaked her out.
- Yeah.

147
00:08:49.863 --> 00:08:52.490
Listen. I got a technician in Woodbury.

148
00:08:52.574 --> 00:08:55.410
It's worth the trek.
I'm going to send you his info.

149
00:08:55.493 --> 00:08:58.788
No. I'll just... I'll take him to Quick Fix
if I can't figure it out.

150
00:08:58.872 --> 00:09:00.915
That place is for morons.
Don't take him there.

151
00:09:00.999 --> 00:09:05.503
My guy will fix him for a third
of the cost. You tell Russ I sent ya.

152
00:09:05.587 --> 00:09:08.465
Okay. Okay. got to go. Thank you.

153
00:09:08.548 --> 00:09:10.759
Mika? Mika?

154
00:09:12.427 --> 00:09:14.179
Come on. kiddo. we gotta boogie.

155
00:09:14.262 --> 00:09:17.724
I don't want to go to school.
I want to be with Yang.

156
00:09:17.807 --> 00:09:21.019
Mika. the longer we wait. the worse
it's gonna be for Yang.

157
00:09:21.102 --> 00:09:22.437
What do you mean?

158
00:09:22.520 --> 00:09:24.856
He'll start decomposing.

159
00:09:24.939 --> 00:09:26.149
What?

160
00:09:26.232 --> 00:09:28.568
Come on. we gotta go.

161
00:09:28.651 --> 00:09:30.153
Mika. now.

162
00:09:33.531 --> 00:09:35.992
<i>FYI. Mika's going to be with me
for the day.</i>

163
00:09:36.076 --> 00:09:38.078
[Kyra] <i>Why? What happened?</i>

164
00:09:38.161 --> 00:09:42.582
Well. you know. she just refused
and I wasn't gonna drag her inside.

165
00:09:42.665 --> 00:09:44.250
<i>Mika?</i>

166
00:09:44.334 --> 00:09:45.335
[Mika groans]

167
00:09:47.629 --> 00:09:49.255
<i>Answer me.</i>

168
00:09:49.339 --> 00:09:53.635
Mom. I can't. I want to be with Yang.

169
00:09:53.718 --> 00:09:56.805
<i>It's okay. darling.
I just wanted to hear your voice.</i>

170
00:09:56.888 --> 00:09:59.516
<i>You need to listen to Dad
and be good and calm. okay?</i>

171
00:09:59.599 --> 00:10:02.185
- Is Yang going to be better?
- Yes. he's gonna be...

172
00:10:02.268 --> 00:10:04.729
[Kyra] <i>Well. we don't know
for sure. but...</i>

173
00:10:04.813 --> 00:10:06.106
What do you mean?

174
00:10:06.189 --> 00:10:07.649
Yeah. what do you mean?

175
00:10:07.732 --> 00:10:10.610
<i>We can't make any promises.
but. Mika. listen.</i>

176
00:10:10.693 --> 00:10:13.530
<i>if you can be good and calm
for the rest of the day.</i>

177
00:10:13.613 --> 00:10:15.490
<i>I'm gonna bring you a surprise.</i>

178
00:10:15.573 --> 00:10:16.658
What?

179
00:10:16.741 --> 00:10:18.535
You just promised her a surprise.

180
00:10:18.618 --> 00:10:20.036
- What is it. Mom?
<i>- That's different.</i>

181
00:10:20.120 --> 00:10:22.789
- Mom. what is it?
<i>- I wasn't trying to...</i>

182
00:10:24.582 --> 00:10:26.000
<i>I appreciate you taking the day off.</i>

183
00:10:26.084 --> 00:10:27.335
Mom?

184
00:10:27.418 --> 00:10:29.212
<i>Honey. be good and listen to Dad.</i>

185
00:10:29.295 --> 00:10:31.548
<i>Oh. I need to go. I have to get ready
for my presentation.</i>

186
00:10:31.631 --> 00:10:32.882
<i>- We'll talk.</i>
- [call ends]

187
00:10:33.925 --> 00:10:35.927
What is she gonna get me. Dad?

188
00:10:37.887 --> 00:10:41.683
- I have no idea.
- I think I know.

189
00:10:43.268 --> 00:10:45.895
Just don't get your hopes up
for anything specific.

190
00:10:47.230 --> 00:10:50.441
[whispers] <i>Gege.</i> I know
what she's gonna get me.

191
00:10:54.863 --> 00:10:56.281
[Jake] Excuse me?

192
00:10:58.241 --> 00:11:00.952
- Excuse me?
- Can I help you?

193
00:11:01.035 --> 00:11:03.663
Yeah. I was wondering if you could...
I purchased a...

194
00:11:04.664 --> 00:11:06.457
This used to be a store
where you could buy. uh.

195
00:11:06.541 --> 00:11:08.710
an older sibling for Chinese adoptions.

196
00:11:08.793 --> 00:11:10.628
It was called Second Siblings.

197
00:11:14.841 --> 00:11:16.551
We sell fish and tanks.

198
00:11:16.634 --> 00:11:19.679
Yeah. I can see. but do you know
what happened to that shop?

199
00:11:19.762 --> 00:11:22.765
Before my store. they sold memory.

200
00:11:22.849 --> 00:11:26.728
Memory-balia. Is that how
you say it. memory-balia?

201
00:11:26.811 --> 00:11:31.232
- Memorabilia.
- Memorabilia. Yeah. memories.

202
00:11:31.316 --> 00:11:33.151
But no technos?

203
00:11:33.234 --> 00:11:37.238
No. I'm not sure what it was before that.

204
00:11:37.322 --> 00:11:39.324
All right. thank you.

205
00:11:40.783 --> 00:11:41.618
Mika?

206
00:11:45.163 --> 00:11:47.582
Mika. Mika. come on. let's go.

207
00:11:50.043 --> 00:11:51.669
I want a fish.

208
00:11:55.924 --> 00:11:58.927
[whispers] <i>Gege?</i> Meet Puffy.

209
00:12:02.096 --> 00:12:04.599
Uh. it's a black box issue. okay?

210
00:12:04.682 --> 00:12:06.267
Uh. so by law. we're not allowed to tamper

211
00:12:06.351 --> 00:12:08.770
with the. uh. core interior.
unfortunately.

212
00:12:08.853 --> 00:12:10.230
So what is it that you do here?

213
00:12:10.313 --> 00:12:13.024
Uh. well. we are certified
with Brothers & Sisters. Incorporated.

214
00:12:13.107 --> 00:12:17.445
to repair or replace up to 12 parts
most commonly in need of service.

215
00:12:17.528 --> 00:12:21.532
If you want to take a gander there
at the 12-point diagnostic.

216
00:12:21.616 --> 00:12:23.117
Yeah. but your diagnostics is just...

217
00:12:23.201 --> 00:12:26.162
Um. well. we hooked up Yang
to our certified analyzer.

218
00:12:26.246 --> 00:12:28.581
and. uh. all 12 parts
were in working order.

219
00:12:28.665 --> 00:12:30.375
However. the readout did indicate

220
00:12:30.458 --> 00:12:33.795
that there was a core malfunction.
unfortunately. so...

221
00:12:33.878 --> 00:12:36.089
So what? So there's nothing you can do?

222
00:12:36.172 --> 00:12:37.757
Oh. there's a couple things
we can do here.

223
00:12:37.840 --> 00:12:40.677
Um. we can have him recycled
at Brothers & Sisters.

224
00:12:40.760 --> 00:12:43.846
Uh. if you do so before
he begins to decompose.

225
00:12:43.930 --> 00:12:46.808
you'll get $1.000 off on a new model.
which is great.

226
00:12:46.891 --> 00:12:49.352
If you don't want to have him recycled.
which I completely understand.

227
00:12:49.435 --> 00:12:51.020
we are equipped to turn his head

228
00:12:51.104 --> 00:12:54.315
and his voice box
into a virtual assistant.

229
00:12:54.399 --> 00:12:56.901
and we'd salvage
the remaining parts for ya.

230
00:12:56.985 --> 00:12:58.236
What?

231
00:12:58.319 --> 00:13:00.822
But we would have to send the core
to. uh. Brothers & Sisters.

232
00:13:00.905 --> 00:13:03.116
No. no. no. That's not gonna happen.
No. just give him back to me.

233
00:13:03.199 --> 00:13:04.951
- and I'll get a second opinion.
- Oh. sure. Of course.

234
00:13:05.034 --> 00:13:07.453
Uh. so that'll be 250
for the diagnostics. please.

235
00:13:07.537 --> 00:13:09.038
You're kidding me.

236
00:13:10.415 --> 00:13:11.666
Unfortunately. no.

237
00:13:12.792 --> 00:13:14.794
[indistinct. animated chatter]

238
00:13:38.026 --> 00:13:39.694
[Kyra on speakerphone]
<i>That doesn't sound good.</i>

239
00:13:39.777 --> 00:13:41.070
[Jake] I know.

240
00:13:42.322 --> 00:13:43.948
<i>What did you tell Mika?</i>

241
00:13:44.032 --> 00:13:46.200
I said we were getting
a second opinion.

242
00:13:46.284 --> 00:13:49.287
It's already taken longer
than I expected.

243
00:13:49.370 --> 00:13:51.080
- [Mika] Daddy?
- [Kyra] <i>Hi. Mika.</i>

244
00:13:51.164 --> 00:13:52.623
[Mika] Hi.

245
00:13:52.707 --> 00:13:53.791
<i>Are you okay?</i>

246
00:13:53.875 --> 00:13:57.378
No. I got a fish.

247
00:13:57.462 --> 00:13:59.630
[Kyra] <i>You did?</i>

248
00:13:59.714 --> 00:14:01.257
<i>- She did?</i>
- [Mika] Yeah.

249
00:14:01.341 --> 00:14:05.094
Yeah. it's a little... I'll explain later.
We're almost there.

250
00:14:06.679 --> 00:14:10.141
<i>- All right. Keep me posted.</i>
- Okay.

251
00:14:10.224 --> 00:14:11.893
<i>Bye. Mika.</i>

252
00:14:11.976 --> 00:14:14.937
Bye. Say bye to Yang.

253
00:14:16.814 --> 00:14:17.940
<i>Bye. Yang.</i>

254
00:14:28.493 --> 00:14:31.496
[Russ] It is an interior core problem.

255
00:14:31.579 --> 00:14:33.456
[Jake] Yeah. we knew that already.

256
00:14:33.539 --> 00:14:36.751
I need your permission
to break open the core.

257
00:14:39.295 --> 00:14:41.297
- It's against the law.
- [laughing]

258
00:14:44.801 --> 00:14:47.553
It's just...
It's a bunch of corporate bullshit.

259
00:14:49.389 --> 00:14:51.391
Do you know who made that a law?

260
00:14:51.474 --> 00:14:53.393
Brothers & Sisters.

261
00:14:53.476 --> 00:14:56.437
They're just trying
to protect their spyware.

262
00:14:56.521 --> 00:14:58.689
You recycle that.

263
00:14:58.773 --> 00:15:02.527
they will have so much data
on your family. it'll make your head spin.

264
00:15:03.528 --> 00:15:04.737
[Jake] I'm not interested.

265
00:15:06.197 --> 00:15:07.198
Your loss.

266
00:15:08.408 --> 00:15:10.993
- You promised to fix him.
- Mika. I said wait outside.

267
00:15:11.077 --> 00:15:12.829
You said he was gonna be fine.

268
00:15:19.502 --> 00:15:22.964
Come on. man.
You gotta make a decision.

269
00:15:31.097 --> 00:15:33.266
[Kyra] <i>Maybe this is a good thing.</i>

270
00:15:33.349 --> 00:15:34.851
[Jake] <i>How is this a good thing?</i>

271
00:15:37.270 --> 00:15:39.188
Yang has been...

272
00:15:39.272 --> 00:15:40.940
Yang has been wonderful.

273
00:15:42.442 --> 00:15:45.236
And we'd all miss him terribly. but...

274
00:15:45.319 --> 00:15:46.320
[sighs]

275
00:15:46.404 --> 00:15:48.239
We've been over-reliant on him.

276
00:15:51.117 --> 00:15:55.163
We bought Yang to connect Mika
to her Chinese heritage. not to raise her.

277
00:15:55.246 --> 00:15:57.957
Yeah. but we spent a lot of money on Yang.
I mean. I'm not gonna...

278
00:15:59.542 --> 00:16:03.754
you know. feel bad if he does more
for Mika than teach her Chinese fun facts.

279
00:16:03.838 --> 00:16:07.175
He does a lot more than that.
but you're missing the point.

280
00:16:07.258 --> 00:16:08.509
What's the point?

281
00:16:09.802 --> 00:16:14.390
If we can't fix Yang. we're not gonna buy
another sibling for Mika.

282
00:16:16.726 --> 00:16:17.894
That would just be...

283
00:16:19.061 --> 00:16:20.480
strange.

284
00:16:22.231 --> 00:16:24.066
And we can't afford it anyway.

285
00:16:25.526 --> 00:16:30.198
So we need to be more involved.
more than we are now.

286
00:16:31.199 --> 00:16:33.451
And not just in raising her.

287
00:16:33.534 --> 00:16:36.913
in connecting Mika
to her culture and heritage.

288
00:16:36.996 --> 00:16:38.414
Like. that will be on us.

289
00:16:40.124 --> 00:16:42.960
So we need to be ready and willing.

290
00:17:45.731 --> 00:17:48.734
[tranquil music playing]

291
00:17:58.619 --> 00:18:02.331
- [Yang] Mei. <i>what's wrong?</i>
- [Mika] <i>Nothing.</i>

292
00:18:04.166 --> 00:18:06.168
[Yang] Your face says something different.

293
00:18:08.713 --> 00:18:10.131
[Mika] Just some kids.

294
00:18:11.591 --> 00:18:12.925
In your class?

295
00:18:13.009 --> 00:18:16.012
No. kids at recess.

296
00:18:16.095 --> 00:18:18.598
They were asking
about my real parents.

297
00:18:19.640 --> 00:18:22.184
I see.

298
00:18:22.268 --> 00:18:23.686
And what did you say?

299
00:18:29.317 --> 00:18:31.652
I told them about Mom and Dad.

300
00:18:31.736 --> 00:18:35.615
and they said. "No. your real parents."

301
00:18:35.698 --> 00:18:40.119
They said Mom and Dad weren't
really my parents. Not really.

302
00:18:41.454 --> 00:18:42.955
Do you believe them?

303
00:18:45.791 --> 00:18:49.795
I mean. they're our parents. but...

304
00:18:51.881 --> 00:18:52.965
we're not...

305
00:18:54.175 --> 00:18:57.178
you know. they're not...

306
00:18:59.221 --> 00:19:00.640
Not really.

307
00:19:03.517 --> 00:19:04.644
[Yang] <i>Mei mei.</i>

308
00:19:08.481 --> 00:19:09.607
Here it is.

309
00:19:10.983 --> 00:19:12.568
Take a look at this.

310
00:19:13.986 --> 00:19:16.447
Is the tree hurt?

311
00:19:16.530 --> 00:19:19.825
No. Something wonderful
is happening here.

312
00:19:19.909 --> 00:19:21.410
What?

313
00:19:21.494 --> 00:19:25.498
You see. this branch
is from a different tree.

314
00:19:25.581 --> 00:19:27.375
It is?

315
00:19:27.458 --> 00:19:32.088
Yes. but now it's becoming
an actual part of this tree.

316
00:19:32.171 --> 00:19:36.300
Not really. though. It's just pretend.

317
00:19:36.384 --> 00:19:37.635
Why do you say that?

318
00:19:37.718 --> 00:19:40.554
Because it's just taped to the tree.

319
00:19:41.764 --> 00:19:45.768
Oh. right. It looks like that. doesn't it?

320
00:19:46.977 --> 00:19:49.980
Here. let's find one
that's already attached.

321
00:20:05.413 --> 00:20:06.414
<i>Mei mei.</i>

322
00:20:10.626 --> 00:20:12.586
See this branch?

323
00:20:12.670 --> 00:20:15.464
This branch is also from another tree.

324
00:20:15.548 --> 00:20:18.843
But look. you're connected
to Mom and Dad.

325
00:20:18.926 --> 00:20:21.262
just like this branch.

326
00:20:21.345 --> 00:20:24.348
You're a part of the family tree.
For real.

327
00:20:25.599 --> 00:20:28.227
Then so are you.

328
00:20:30.020 --> 00:20:31.522
Why do they do it?

329
00:20:31.605 --> 00:20:34.400
Why do they move branches
to different trees?

330
00:20:34.483 --> 00:20:37.778
It's called grafting.
They do it to make something new.

331
00:20:37.862 --> 00:20:41.115
Some of the apples you love were produced
by combining different trees.

332
00:20:41.198 --> 00:20:45.202
It's an ancient technique that was used
in China over 4.000 years ago.

333
00:20:45.286 --> 00:20:47.913
- A Chinese fun fact.
- Yes.

334
00:20:47.997 --> 00:20:50.916
But you should know
that both trees are important.

335
00:20:51.917 --> 00:20:55.171
Not just this one. but the one
from this branch. too.

336
00:20:56.172 --> 00:20:59.258
Your other family tree is also
a vital part of who you are.

337
00:21:00.342 --> 00:21:01.343
Do you understand?

338
00:21:13.939 --> 00:21:15.149
I want to go with Dad.

339
00:21:15.232 --> 00:21:17.485
No. kiddo. you need to go to school today.

340
00:21:17.568 --> 00:21:21.113
But Yang! I wanna see Yang!

341
00:21:21.197 --> 00:21:24.742
Hey. what about your Pup-Pup?
Don't you want to show your friends?

342
00:21:24.825 --> 00:21:27.745
- Yang.
- Yang's gonna be home soon.

343
00:21:27.828 --> 00:21:30.247
- Is he better?
- We'll see.

344
00:21:32.625 --> 00:21:34.168
[Kyra] But you need
to go to school.

345
00:21:34.251 --> 00:21:36.587
Yang would want that. Do it for <i>gege.</i>

346
00:21:38.798 --> 00:21:40.508
He'd want me to show my Pup-Pup.

347
00:21:40.591 --> 00:21:42.426
- [Kyra] Mm-hmm.
- All right. I'm heading out.

348
00:21:42.510 --> 00:21:44.720
- Okay. Let me know how it goes.
- Will do.

349
00:21:47.473 --> 00:21:49.892
[Kyra] Your bag. Come on.

350
00:22:00.736 --> 00:22:04.073
[car door opens and closes]

351
00:22:06.867 --> 00:22:09.870
[tranquil music playing]

352
00:22:52.830 --> 00:22:57.626
[Russ] <i>We've always known that some bots
are equipped with spyware.</i>

353
00:22:57.710 --> 00:23:00.671
Especially the foreign ones.
And now we have proof.

354
00:23:01.672 --> 00:23:04.675
Now? So you've never seen these before.

355
00:23:04.758 --> 00:23:06.969
What does it matter? It is what it is.

356
00:23:10.472 --> 00:23:12.099
- Have you looked at the recordings?
- No.

357
00:23:13.893 --> 00:23:15.352
No! I'm pro-privacy.

358
00:23:15.436 --> 00:23:18.105
Can I see what's on here?

359
00:23:18.188 --> 00:23:19.356
You'll need a special reader.

360
00:23:19.440 --> 00:23:22.109
The connectors.
they're nothing I've seen before.

361
00:23:22.192 --> 00:23:25.195
[chuckles] This is
some high-level shit. man.

362
00:23:28.574 --> 00:23:29.783
I mean. this is...

363
00:23:31.577 --> 00:23:34.997
Sorry. I'm... I'm just trying
to wrap my head around it.

364
00:23:39.209 --> 00:23:40.836
- It's disturbing.
- Yes.

365
00:23:43.756 --> 00:23:45.174
It is disturbing.

366
00:23:47.885 --> 00:23:49.511
It's time to wake up. man.

367
00:23:52.389 --> 00:23:53.349
[Jake sighs]

368
00:23:57.978 --> 00:24:02.942
So how do I buy a reader
that I can see what's on this?

369
00:24:03.025 --> 00:24:05.653
No one's selling a reader for that.

370
00:24:08.030 --> 00:24:11.367
You'll have to have one specifically
modified for those connectors.

371
00:24:12.576 --> 00:24:13.577
Great.

372
00:24:24.004 --> 00:24:27.299
Okay. I'm gonna give you a name.

373
00:24:28.467 --> 00:24:31.679
There's no number.
but this is where you find them.

374
00:24:48.862 --> 00:24:50.072
How much do I owe you?

375
00:24:51.865 --> 00:24:54.076
Like I said. I get paid to fix things.

376
00:24:56.370 --> 00:24:57.413
Thank you.

377
00:24:59.164 --> 00:25:01.000
I guess I'll take Yang back.

378
00:25:03.877 --> 00:25:04.878
I'll tell you what.

379
00:25:07.131 --> 00:25:09.550
Why don't... Why don't you look
what's on there first?

380
00:25:11.468 --> 00:25:14.888
If it's something bad. disturbing...

381
00:25:14.972 --> 00:25:16.390
[chuckles]

382
00:25:16.473 --> 00:25:19.518
You might not want this bot
in your house anymore.

383
00:25:22.980 --> 00:25:27.526
You can take him. but also.
he's gonna start decomposing.

384
00:25:28.902 --> 00:25:31.405
You won't get as much value for him.

385
00:25:32.781 --> 00:25:36.785
I can keep him hooked up on the simulator
until you know more.

386
00:25:41.707 --> 00:25:43.542
You're a friend of George. right?

387
00:25:44.585 --> 00:25:45.586
Yeah.

388
00:25:47.004 --> 00:25:49.006
[man on speaker]
<i>Sorry. she's in a meeting.</i>

389
00:25:49.089 --> 00:25:51.133
<i>but I'd be happy to pass on a message.</i>

390
00:25:51.216 --> 00:25:52.551
Yeah. could you just tell her...

391
00:25:55.471 --> 00:25:57.473
<i>Uh. hello? Are you still there?</i>

392
00:25:58.974 --> 00:26:01.602
You know what? It's all right.
I'll talk to her later.

393
00:26:01.685 --> 00:26:03.312
<i>Great. Should I have her call you back?</i>

394
00:26:03.395 --> 00:26:05.230
No. No. it's all right. Thank you.

395
00:26:06.607 --> 00:26:07.483
[call ends]

396
00:26:18.368 --> 00:26:19.745
[Jake] I was told I could talk to you.

397
00:26:19.828 --> 00:26:21.872
I was looking for Max Walker.
but they mentioned...

398
00:26:21.955 --> 00:26:24.541
- [woman] Oh. I'm not interested.
- Sorry?

399
00:26:24.625 --> 00:26:27.961
[woman] Are you here to talk
some conspiracy shit?

400
00:26:28.045 --> 00:26:30.506
- No. No. Russ told me that I could...
- Russ?

401
00:26:30.589 --> 00:26:33.133
Oh. man. you're one of them. I can't
believe they let you back here.

402
00:26:33.217 --> 00:26:35.052
I'm not one of them. I...

403
00:26:37.596 --> 00:26:38.847
I have this.

404
00:26:40.349 --> 00:26:42.184
I was told Max might be
able to help me with it.

405
00:26:42.267 --> 00:26:45.979
- What is that?
- Russ said it's spyware.

406
00:26:49.566 --> 00:26:50.984
Where did you find it?

407
00:26:52.736 --> 00:26:54.238
It was inside Yang.

408
00:26:54.321 --> 00:26:57.324
And... he's our...

409
00:26:57.407 --> 00:26:59.243
[inhales shakily]

410
00:26:59.326 --> 00:27:01.787
We bought him after we adopted
our daughter. She's Chinese.

411
00:27:01.870 --> 00:27:02.996
Mm-hmm.

412
00:27:03.080 --> 00:27:06.708
And my neighbor recommended Russ
after Yang shut down. and Russ broke in...

413
00:27:06.792 --> 00:27:09.586
Can I... Sorry. Can I?

414
00:27:09.670 --> 00:27:10.754
Yeah. sure.

415
00:27:29.606 --> 00:27:32.401
Holy shit. this isn't spyware.

416
00:27:32.484 --> 00:27:34.319
I'm pretty sure it's a memory bank.

417
00:27:37.406 --> 00:27:41.702
<i>The memory banks allowed the technos
to record a few seconds each day.</i>

418
00:27:41.785 --> 00:27:46.415
<i>The labs were trying to understand
what technos considered memorable.</i>

419
00:27:46.498 --> 00:27:47.916
<i>But the research was uncovered.</i>

420
00:27:48.000 --> 00:27:52.379
<i>the whole project was shut down
immediately for violating privacy laws.</i>

421
00:27:52.462 --> 00:27:54.089
[Jake] <i>So what do I do?</i>

422
00:27:57.009 --> 00:27:58.927
Oh. I'm not gonna lie. This...

423
00:28:00.012 --> 00:28:02.764
This is a big deal.

424
00:28:02.848 --> 00:28:05.475
If it's the regulator. then Russ is right.

425
00:28:05.559 --> 00:28:08.103
He's not gonna turn on.

426
00:28:08.187 --> 00:28:09.897
I'm just being honest with you.

427
00:28:11.899 --> 00:28:16.653
But his existence. Yang's existence

428
00:28:16.737 --> 00:28:20.324
would be an invaluable contribution
to this museum

429
00:28:20.407 --> 00:28:23.577
and just to the whole understanding
of techno-sapiens.

430
00:28:26.955 --> 00:28:30.334
So I guess the real question's gonna be.

431
00:28:30.417 --> 00:28:35.047
what do we pay you to have Yang
and his memories in our collection?

432
00:28:36.215 --> 00:28:38.217
[indistinct chatter]

433
00:28:39.468 --> 00:28:41.470
[Jake] Could I have
another one of these. please?

434
00:28:41.553 --> 00:28:44.556
["Air on the G String" playing on speaker]

435
00:28:47.351 --> 00:28:48.268
[electronic chiming]

436
00:28:53.106 --> 00:28:54.191
[Jake] Answer call.

437
00:28:54.274 --> 00:28:56.985
- Hey.
<i>- Hey. How's Mika?</i>

438
00:28:57.069 --> 00:28:58.070
She's next door.

439
00:28:59.071 --> 00:29:01.531
- Next door? At George's?
<i>- Yep.</i>

440
00:29:01.615 --> 00:29:03.033
Why?

441
00:29:04.534 --> 00:29:07.788
Because you're not here.
and I have work to do.

442
00:29:07.871 --> 00:29:09.915
I'm taking care of Yang.

443
00:29:09.998 --> 00:29:12.584
<i>- Is that what you're doing?</i>
- Yes.

444
00:29:35.315 --> 00:29:37.484
So you just dropped her off over there?

445
00:29:37.567 --> 00:29:39.945
No. his daughters
invited her over to play.

446
00:29:42.406 --> 00:29:44.491
You need to stop being
so hard on George.

447
00:29:44.574 --> 00:29:48.036
He likes you.
and he's being really helpful.

448
00:29:48.120 --> 00:29:49.288
His kids are clones.

449
00:29:49.371 --> 00:29:51.540
I don't want to talk about this again.

450
00:29:51.623 --> 00:29:53.458
And he paints his face
for sporting events.

451
00:29:53.542 --> 00:29:56.253
- What is wrong with you?
- What's wrong with him?

452
00:29:56.336 --> 00:29:58.547
You need to stop. Okay?

453
00:30:03.677 --> 00:30:04.553
[sighs]

454
00:30:07.681 --> 00:30:09.141
How's the ramen?

455
00:30:10.642 --> 00:30:13.645
It's. um. soothing.

456
00:30:14.730 --> 00:30:16.356
Yeah. I can see that.

457
00:30:18.483 --> 00:30:19.651
What are you having?

458
00:30:21.570 --> 00:30:22.529
Ramen.

459
00:30:23.530 --> 00:30:26.241
Really? That's funny.

460
00:30:26.325 --> 00:30:28.076
<i>Is it?</i>

461
00:30:28.160 --> 00:30:30.203
Sort of. don't you think?

462
00:30:30.287 --> 00:30:32.706
Are you any closer to getting Yang fixed?

463
00:30:34.750 --> 00:30:36.960
This is the third place
you've taken him to.

464
00:30:37.044 --> 00:30:38.920
Well. he's actually
still at the repair shop.

465
00:30:39.004 --> 00:30:43.800
I'm. uh. having a part examined.
By a specialist.

466
00:30:43.884 --> 00:30:46.511
So is he gonna be
up and running again soon?

467
00:30:47.512 --> 00:30:52.351
I'm not sure. You know. it's...
it's complicated.

468
00:30:52.434 --> 00:30:53.685
[door closes]

469
00:30:54.853 --> 00:30:56.480
That's Mika. I got to go.

470
00:31:03.278 --> 00:31:05.155
Functions like any other reader.

471
00:31:05.238 --> 00:31:06.740
Should be intuitive.

472
00:31:06.823 --> 00:31:08.533
Do I need a code?

473
00:31:08.617 --> 00:31:11.453
Yeah. there should be a certification card
that came with Yang.

474
00:31:11.536 --> 00:31:14.206
There's a serial number and a PIN on it.

475
00:31:14.289 --> 00:31:17.918
Also. per our agreement. you'll need
to bring Yang's body here tomorrow.

476
00:31:18.001 --> 00:31:19.127
- Sooner the better.
- Yes.

477
00:31:19.211 --> 00:31:24.841
I wouldn't be surprised if Russ is trying
to replace parts and steal the originals.

478
00:31:24.925 --> 00:31:29.471
We will keep Yang's body
preserved here in a bio-state

479
00:31:29.554 --> 00:31:32.349
while you go and review the memories

480
00:31:33.350 --> 00:31:36.395
- and decide what you want to do next.
- Okay.

481
00:31:36.478 --> 00:31:39.064
- Yeah. Thank you.
- Thank you.

482
00:31:39.147 --> 00:31:41.858
I've dedicated my life to understanding
techno-sapiens.

483
00:31:41.942 --> 00:31:44.569
This... This is a gift.

484
00:31:55.038 --> 00:31:56.123
[door closes]

485
00:32:12.848 --> 00:32:14.558
[Mika. singing]
♪ <i>I want to be</i> ♪

486
00:32:14.641 --> 00:32:17.644
♪ <i>Just like the wind</i> ♪

487
00:32:17.727 --> 00:32:21.189
♪ <i>Just flowing in the air</i> ♪

488
00:32:21.273 --> 00:32:24.693
♪ <i>Flowing in open space</i> ♪

489
00:32:25.694 --> 00:32:27.446
[Kyra] Yang taught you that?

490
