742
00:55:39.878 --> 00:55:43.382
- Hey. what can I get for you?
- Hey. do you know her?

743
00:55:43.465 --> 00:55:45.092
Uh. no. I don't.

744
00:55:45.175 --> 00:55:47.010
Could you ask someone else?
I think she used to work here.

745
00:55:47.094 --> 00:55:50.347
I'm sorry. there's a line.
I'm gonna need you to order something.

746
00:55:50.430 --> 00:55:52.432
Oh. I'll have a double espresso.

747
00:55:52.516 --> 00:55:54.226
And if I can speak to the manager.
that would be great.

748
00:55:54.309 --> 00:55:55.894
Double espresso. is that it?

749
00:55:55.978 --> 00:55:57.980
Yes. And the manager.

750
00:56:03.068 --> 00:56:05.028
Sorry. I can't help you.

751
00:56:05.112 --> 00:56:07.739
- But she worked here.
- She doesn't work here anymore.

752
00:56:09.533 --> 00:56:12.870
- But could you tell me her name?
- Why do you want to find her?

753
00:56:15.372 --> 00:56:17.583
She knew my son.

754
00:56:17.666 --> 00:56:21.879
And he's not doing so well right now.
Health-wise.

755
00:56:21.962 --> 00:56:23.881
And I thought she'd want to know.

756
00:56:23.964 --> 00:56:27.301
- But you've never met her.
- No.

757
00:56:27.384 --> 00:56:29.011
And you don't know her name.

758
00:56:30.345 --> 00:56:31.346
No.

759
00:56:32.639 --> 00:56:35.642
Yeah. Then I don't either.

760
00:56:36.768 --> 00:56:37.853
Sorry.

761
00:56:47.863 --> 00:56:49.364
- [George] Hey.
- [Jake] Hey. George.

762
00:56:49.448 --> 00:56:50.449
[George] What do you need?

763
00:56:50.532 --> 00:56:53.952
I was wondering if you'd ever
seen her around the house.

764
00:56:57.497 --> 00:56:59.166
I... Who is she?

765
00:56:59.249 --> 00:57:01.627
I don't know. but Yang knew her.

766
00:57:01.710 --> 00:57:03.587
Really? Huh.

767
00:57:03.670 --> 00:57:05.881
I... I didn't know that bots. uh...

768
00:57:07.758 --> 00:57:12.346
That techno beings could
make friends on their own.

769
00:57:12.429 --> 00:57:14.431
- They were just...
- I-I don't know anything.

770
00:57:14.514 --> 00:57:17.184
- I just want to find her.
- Hmm.

771
00:57:17.267 --> 00:57:19.436
Let me ask the girls.
Maybe they know something.

772
00:57:19.519 --> 00:57:21.104
Please. Thank you.

773
00:57:21.188 --> 00:57:23.523
Ladies. I need to see you.

774
00:57:24.608 --> 00:57:26.401
[Vicky] What is it?

775
00:57:26.485 --> 00:57:29.321
Just get over here.
And bring the twins.

776
00:57:31.073 --> 00:57:33.700
Vicky just made
the all-star softball team.

777
00:57:33.784 --> 00:57:36.244
You gotta come watch.
I mean. she's just great.

778
00:57:36.328 --> 00:57:37.329
Nice.

779
00:57:39.915 --> 00:57:41.166
What is it?

780
00:57:42.376 --> 00:57:47.214
Mr. Fleming wants to know
if you've seen her around.

781
00:57:47.297 --> 00:57:49.299
Are you sure?

782
00:57:50.342 --> 00:57:53.887
- Can we go?
- Yeah. Go ahead.

783
00:57:56.723 --> 00:57:57.975
How about you?

784
00:57:59.643 --> 00:58:01.061
Is she in trouble?

785
00:58:02.062 --> 00:58:04.856
- I don't...
- No. No. not at all.

786
00:58:04.940 --> 00:58:05.941
How's Yang?

787
00:58:07.025 --> 00:58:09.111
He's not so good.

788
00:58:09.194 --> 00:58:12.614
You know. I think finding her.
it might help.

789
00:58:14.366 --> 00:58:17.119
- Yeah. I've seen her.
- You have?

790
00:58:17.202 --> 00:58:19.955
A couple times. At your place.

791
00:58:20.038 --> 00:58:22.040
Did you ever talk to her?

792
00:58:22.124 --> 00:58:24.710
Once. Yang asked me
not to say anything.

793
00:58:24.793 --> 00:58:26.336
Why?

794
00:58:26.420 --> 00:58:28.714
You don't like clones. right?

795
00:58:28.797 --> 00:58:31.591
- No. no. it's not...
- Come on. Vic. No fastballs.

796
00:58:31.675 --> 00:58:32.968
I just... I've never had the...

797
00:58:33.051 --> 00:58:35.470
- It's... It's fine.
- No. it's not.

798
00:58:35.554 --> 00:58:38.348
- Vicky.
- She's a clone.

799
00:58:38.432 --> 00:58:39.808
She is?

800
00:58:39.891 --> 00:58:44.062
Yeah. but she's really cool
and nice. Like most of us.

801
00:58:45.063 --> 00:58:46.523
I'm sure.

802
00:58:48.275 --> 00:58:50.277
Um. do you know her name?

803
00:58:50.360 --> 00:58:54.448
It's Aidy or Ada. something like that.

804
00:58:56.158 --> 00:58:59.077
Okay. Thank you.

805
00:59:00.078 --> 00:59:02.122
- Look. I'm sorry if I've ever...
- Can I go now?

806
00:59:04.791 --> 00:59:07.210
Yes. Thank you. sweetheart.

807
00:59:12.716 --> 00:59:13.967
I'm... I'm really sorry. it's...

808
00:59:14.051 --> 00:59:16.720
No. no. no. it's... Honestly.

809
00:59:16.803 --> 00:59:17.929
You should see her fastball.

810
00:59:18.013 --> 00:59:20.974
I mean. she's just...
[mimics ball whooshing]

811
00:59:21.058 --> 00:59:23.060
...like. all day long. I mean...

812
00:59:25.145 --> 00:59:27.522
Well. thanks. George.
I really have to...

813
00:59:27.606 --> 00:59:29.483
- Another time.
- Yeah.

814
00:59:29.566 --> 00:59:33.862
Uh. hey. maybe we can
get a drink together. huh? Some time?

815
00:59:33.945 --> 00:59:36.448
Yeah. Yeah. that'd be great.

816
00:59:52.714 --> 00:59:54.549
[Mika] I want to see <i>gege.</i>

817
00:59:56.218 --> 00:59:57.427
I know. love.

818
00:59:58.428 --> 01:00:03.058
You miss him? Me. too.
We just can't see him now.

819
01:00:05.393 --> 01:00:08.021
What about the family dance?

820
01:00:08.105 --> 01:00:10.315
Are we never gonna dance again?

821
01:00:10.398 --> 01:00:12.234
[Kyra] Of course we will.

822
01:00:13.235 --> 01:00:17.864
But we might have to compete
in the family of threes.

823
01:00:19.116 --> 01:00:22.619
- I don't want to be a family of three!
- Mika.

824
01:00:22.702 --> 01:00:24.913
I want <i>gege</i> back!

825
01:00:27.833 --> 01:00:31.211
[Kyra] Daddy's trying his best.
He's doing everything he can.

826
01:00:31.294 --> 01:00:32.921
I want him back. too.

827
01:00:36.258 --> 01:00:40.262
What about you. Mom?
Do you want him back?

828
01:00:42.347 --> 01:00:43.765
Of course I do.

829
01:00:52.774 --> 01:00:54.776
[Kyra] This is dragging on too long.

830
01:00:56.653 --> 01:01:01.825
- [Jake] I just need a little more time.
- We need to start focusing on Mika.

831
01:01:01.908 --> 01:01:04.327
We're just making things
more difficult for her.

832
01:01:07.914 --> 01:01:11.918
Jake. do you hear me?

833
01:01:15.255 --> 01:01:19.759
If we can't get Yang fixed. we just...
we need to move forward. Okay?

834
01:01:19.843 --> 01:01:21.678
Now. Now.

835
01:01:23.180 --> 01:01:25.182
[Jake] I need to tell you something.

836
01:01:45.076 --> 01:01:46.369
[Jake] <i>No. it's... it's frozen.</i>

837
01:01:46.453 --> 01:01:47.913
That's interesting.

838
01:01:47.996 --> 01:01:51.833
Try command "memory reveal info." and it
should tell you if it's corrupt or not.

839
01:01:51.917 --> 01:01:52.918
Okay. I'll do that.

840
01:01:53.001 --> 01:01:55.295
Also. I was wondering.

841
01:01:55.378 --> 01:01:59.174
is it possible for cultural technos
like Yang to...

842
01:02:00.508 --> 01:02:02.719
want to have romantic potential?

843
01:02:02.802 --> 01:02:04.429
Do you mean
for humans to use them?

844
01:02:04.512 --> 01:02:08.600
No. no. no. I mean. for Yang
to be interested in...

845
01:02:08.683 --> 01:02:11.770
There's a girl. and she showed up
in his memories.

846
01:02:11.853 --> 01:02:14.522
and. you know. we didn't know
anything about her.

847
01:02:14.606 --> 01:02:15.732
Really?

848
01:02:16.733 --> 01:02:17.943
That's fascinating.

849
01:02:18.026 --> 01:02:21.029
because I've never heard of cultural
technos having that capacity.

850
01:02:21.112 --> 01:02:23.240
I cannot tell you how much...

851
01:02:23.323 --> 01:02:25.242
- [doorbell chimes]
- ...Yang and his memories...

852
01:02:25.325 --> 01:02:26.993
I should get that.

853
01:02:27.077 --> 01:02:29.412
Oh. all right. okay.
But we'll touch base soon?

854
01:02:29.496 --> 01:02:31.206
- Yeah. let's do that.
- Great.

855
01:02:31.289 --> 01:02:32.624
[doorbell chimes]

856
01:02:37.462 --> 01:02:38.713
You've been looking for me?

857
01:02:39.714 --> 01:02:40.757
Yes.

858
01:02:42.050 --> 01:02:44.970
- I'm Jake.
- I know.

859
01:02:46.346 --> 01:02:47.973
I'm Ada.

860
01:02:48.056 --> 01:02:51.184
Ada. Well. come in. please.

861
01:02:52.227 --> 01:02:54.229
I knew something was wrong.

862
01:02:57.357 --> 01:03:00.360
We usually meet.
and he wasn't answering my messages.

863
01:03:03.905 --> 01:03:05.323
I'm sorry.

864
01:03:08.868 --> 01:03:10.287
I'm sorry.

865
01:03:12.080 --> 01:03:14.499
I know Yang loves
being a part of this family.

866
01:03:22.966 --> 01:03:24.384
Can I ask how you met?

867
01:03:25.969 --> 01:03:27.387
At the coffee shop.

868
01:03:29.431 --> 01:03:30.640
He approached you?

869
01:03:33.143 --> 01:03:35.145
He was a regular customer.

870
01:03:36.646 --> 01:03:38.815
He used to buy things
all the time. which. you know.

871
01:03:38.898 --> 01:03:41.151
was funny when I found out
he was a techno.

872
01:03:41.234 --> 01:03:42.152
[chuckles softly]

873
01:03:43.653 --> 01:03:45.280
But. yeah. we started talking. and...

874
01:03:47.490 --> 01:03:50.118
eventually. he asked me
if I wanted to do something.

875
01:03:52.078 --> 01:03:53.413
Were you and Yang...

876
01:03:54.581 --> 01:03:55.832
Were you guys...

877
01:04:00.795 --> 01:04:01.796
[chuckles]

878
01:04:06.134 --> 01:04:09.137
Well. we never really
talked about us in that way.

879
01:04:22.650 --> 01:04:23.693
[electronic beeping]

880
01:04:25.445 --> 01:04:27.405
Sorry. that's... That's my wife.

881
01:04:27.489 --> 01:04:29.157
- I need to...
- [electronic beeping]

882
01:04:29.240 --> 01:04:30.241
- Yeah.
- Sorry.

883
01:04:30.325 --> 01:04:32.786
Please... don't leave.

884
01:04:32.869 --> 01:04:34.496
[electronic beeping continues]

885
01:04:37.749 --> 01:04:40.293
She's freaking out.
You need to pick her up.

886
01:04:40.377 --> 01:04:41.753
What's she doing?

887
01:04:41.836 --> 01:04:44.464
They said she punched a kid. and then
she started screaming at everyone.

888
01:04:44.547 --> 01:04:46.716
- Holy shit.
- Are you able to get her now?

889
01:04:46.800 --> 01:04:49.469
Yeah. Uh. yeah. I'm on my way.

890
01:04:49.552 --> 01:04:51.638
[sighs] Thank you.

891
01:04:54.224 --> 01:04:56.226
I want to see him.

892
01:05:01.481 --> 01:05:02.524
[Ada] Mika...

893
01:05:05.193 --> 01:05:06.820
Yang loves you so much.

894
01:05:07.987 --> 01:05:10.198
He always talks about you.

895
01:05:14.202 --> 01:05:15.161
[Mika cries]

896
01:05:34.139 --> 01:05:36.516
- [Jake] Thanks again for this.
- [Cleo] Oh. I understand.

897
01:05:36.599 --> 01:05:38.017
I'm sure everyone misses him a lot.

898
01:05:42.105 --> 01:05:43.189
Mika.

899
01:05:49.362 --> 01:05:50.989
<i>Gege.</i>

900
01:05:55.410 --> 01:05:56.703
<i>Gege.</i>

901
01:05:57.704 --> 01:05:59.289
[Jake] I'm sorry. baby.

902
01:06:00.290 --> 01:06:01.416
<i>Gege!</i>

903
01:06:01.499 --> 01:06:04.502
[melancholic music playing]

904
01:06:49.631 --> 01:06:51.633
He would have his own area.

905
01:06:54.844 --> 01:07:00.433
We could put some
of his memories on a loop.

906
01:07:01.851 --> 01:07:03.019
projected.

907
01:07:04.020 --> 01:07:08.441
or on a set of readers
that visitors could wear.

908
01:07:16.115 --> 01:07:20.119
Of course. any memory would
have to be approved by you.

909
01:07:32.090 --> 01:07:35.093
[melancholic music continues playing]

910
01:08:21.806 --> 01:08:22.974
Yang.

911
01:08:54.756 --> 01:08:56.049
[Kyra] Play.

912
01:09:18.446 --> 01:09:19.697
[sighs]

913
01:09:23.993 --> 01:09:25.453
[Kyra] <i>Your collection is growing.</i>

914
01:09:26.454 --> 01:09:28.623
Oh. hi.

915
01:09:28.706 --> 01:09:30.291
Yes. it's getting bigger.

916
01:09:31.542 --> 01:09:33.378
Do you want me to stop now?
I can put some away.

917
01:09:33.461 --> 01:09:36.339
No. no. I'm not complaining.

918
01:09:36.422 --> 01:09:38.800
[chuckles] I like them quite a bit.

919
01:09:38.883 --> 01:09:40.510
<i>Do you know butterflies were one</i>

920
01:09:40.593 --> 01:09:44.138
of the favorite subjects
of Chinese trade art in the mid-1800s?

921
01:09:44.222 --> 01:09:45.890
No. I did not know that.

922
01:09:45.973 --> 01:09:48.142
The Chinese love butterflies.

923
01:09:49.143 --> 01:09:51.187
There's also a famous
folk tale about two lovers

924
01:09:51.270 --> 01:09:54.107
who die of broken hearts
and reemerge as butterflies.

925
01:09:54.190 --> 01:09:58.069
Also. the ancient Chinese
philosopher Lao Tzu once said.

926
01:09:58.152 --> 01:10:00.196
"What the caterpillar calls the end.

927
01:10:00.279 --> 01:10:02.657
the rest of the world calls a butterfly."

928
01:10:04.409 --> 01:10:05.410
[laughs]

929
01:10:06.536 --> 01:10:07.537
I like that.

930
01:10:08.996 --> 01:10:10.665
I like that. [laughs]

931
01:10:16.754 --> 01:10:18.381
Is this something you believe?

932
01:10:18.464 --> 01:10:20.925
- Hmm?
- That the end...

933
01:10:21.008 --> 01:10:24.137
That the end is also a beginning?

934
01:10:24.220 --> 01:10:27.348
...is also the beginning?

935
01:10:31.060 --> 01:10:32.061
For the caterpillar...

936
01:10:32.145 --> 01:10:34.731
For the caterpillar. yes.

937
01:10:36.607 --> 01:10:39.026
But do you believe
it's true for all things?

938
01:10:42.572 --> 01:10:47.660
I don't know. I'm not programmed
to believe in that way.

939
01:10:47.744 --> 01:10:49.162
What about you?

940
01:10:54.250 --> 01:10:56.085
I'd like to believe that.

941
01:10:56.169 --> 01:10:58.588
- Do you?
- [laughs]

942
01:10:58.671 --> 01:10:59.547
[Yang] Do you?

943
01:11:00.798 --> 01:11:01.799
[chuckles softly]

944
01:11:03.843 --> 01:11:06.721
Sometimes I think

945
01:11:06.804 --> 01:11:10.266
humans are programmed
to believe in such things. but...

946
01:11:14.687 --> 01:11:17.106
I don't know if it's really
in our best interest.

947
01:11:20.318 --> 01:11:22.320
May I be honest with you?

948
01:11:23.488 --> 01:11:26.908
Yes. Wait. is...

949
01:11:26.991 --> 01:11:28.826
Is not being honest
an option for you?

950
01:11:28.910 --> 01:11:30.912
I don't think so.

951
01:11:32.622 --> 01:11:34.707
[laughs] Hmm.

952
01:11:38.252 --> 01:11:39.253
Go on.

953
01:11:44.592 --> 01:11:50.014
I'm fine if there's nothing in the end.

954
01:11:54.685 --> 01:11:55.895
Are you?

955
01:11:58.397 --> 01:12:00.817
Maybe I was programmed
this way as well.

956
01:12:13.204 --> 01:12:15.206
Does it ever make you feel sad?

957
01:12:19.794 --> 01:12:20.795
[chuckles lightly]

958
01:12:23.881 --> 01:12:24.757
Um...

959
01:12:25.883 --> 01:12:29.512
There's no something
without nothing.

960
01:12:40.314 --> 01:12:43.526
Does it ever make you feel sad?

961
01:12:43.609 --> 01:12:48.030
There's no something without nothing.

962
01:12:49.740 --> 01:12:52.201
Lao Tzu?

963
01:12:52.285 --> 01:12:53.578
I'm not sure.

964
01:13:17.393 --> 01:13:19.812
[Jake] Did Yang ever struggle
with being a techno?

965
01:13:24.775 --> 01:13:26.027
What do you mean?

966
01:13:27.320 --> 01:13:31.324
I mean. did he ever... want to be human?

967
01:13:32.825 --> 01:13:34.368
[chuckles]

968
01:13:36.162 --> 01:13:37.580
What?

969
01:13:39.332 --> 01:13:40.750
Nothing.

970
01:13:44.795 --> 01:13:48.799
It's just... That's such a human thing
to ask. isn't it?

971
01:13:49.800 --> 01:13:52.219
We always assume that other beings
would want to be human.

972
01:13:52.303 --> 01:13:54.263
What's so great about being human?

973
01:13:55.264 --> 01:14:00.102
So he never struggled with it?
He never... questioned it?

974
01:14:03.814 --> 01:14:05.066
Not to me.

975
01:14:08.069 --> 01:14:09.695
I see.

976
01:14:17.411 --> 01:14:19.413
He did question if he was Chinese.

977
01:14:21.415 --> 01:14:22.833
He did?

978
01:14:24.919 --> 01:14:25.920
Yeah.

979
01:14:30.841 --> 01:14:33.844
"What makes someone Asian?"

980
01:14:36.889 --> 01:14:38.891
He'd ask that all the time.

981
01:14:40.935 --> 01:14:44.563
Maybe he just wanted to help Mika
understand what it means to be Chinese.

982
01:14:48.484 --> 01:14:50.486
He was dedicated to his little sister.

983
01:14:56.242 --> 01:14:57.868
Yeah. Yang was a good brother.

984
01:15:01.038 --> 01:15:03.457
He's a great brother.

985
01:15:07.128 --> 01:15:09.130
[wind chimes ringing]

986
01:15:37.908 --> 01:15:39.910
[soft music playing]

987
01:16:13.486 --> 01:16:15.488
[rain falling]

988
01:16:51.398 --> 01:16:53.317
[Jake] Reveal file info.

989
01:16:53.400 --> 01:16:55.694
[reader] <i>Wrong command. Try again.</i>

990
01:16:57.196 --> 01:17:00.449
Reveal memory info.

991
01:17:00.533 --> 01:17:03.452
[reader] <i>Access granted. Beta archive.</i>

992
01:17:03.536 --> 01:17:04.954
Beta archive.

993
01:17:06.372 --> 01:17:07.373
Open.

994
01:17:07.456 --> 01:17:10.960
<i>- Wrong command. Try again.</i>
- Extract.

995
01:17:11.043 --> 01:17:13.754
<i>- Full command.</i>
- Extract beta.

996
01:17:24.348 --> 01:17:25.432
Play all.

997
01:17:39.363 --> 01:17:40.990
[baby crying in other room]

998
01:17:52.501 --> 01:17:53.586
Zoom in.

999
01:18:00.968 --> 01:18:02.219
Coordinates.

1000
01:18:07.766 --> 01:18:10.811
- Hello.
- [Jake] Hi. could I speak to the owners?

1001
01:18:10.895 --> 01:18:12.313
Uh. yes. One moment.

1002
01:18:17.234 --> 01:18:19.820
[Nancy] <i>He wasn't just quiet.</i>

1003
01:18:19.904 --> 01:18:22.114
<i>He seemed despondent. Broken.</i>

1004
01:18:23.115 --> 01:18:26.535
We took him back a few days later.
and they let us make an exchange.

1005
01:18:26.619 --> 01:18:27.828
Brothers & Sisters?

1006
01:18:27.912 --> 01:18:29.538
No. it was. uh...

1007
01:18:31.874 --> 01:18:33.959
Well. I can't remember the name.

1008
01:18:34.043 --> 01:18:35.669
We didn't buy him new.

1009
01:18:37.004 --> 01:18:38.464
You didn't?

1010
01:18:38.547 --> 01:18:40.174
No. but he was certified.

1011
01:18:41.717 --> 01:18:43.510
Second Siblings.

1012
01:18:43.594 --> 01:18:46.597
- Maybe. Is that in Chinatown?
- Yeah. it used to be.

1013
01:18:48.307 --> 01:18:52.770
I assume he was on when you
bought him in a sleep state?

1014
01:18:52.853 --> 01:18:54.271
That sounds right.

1015
01:18:58.734 --> 01:18:59.568
[Jake sighs]

1016
01:19:00.819 --> 01:19:01.946
[Jake] Extract...

1017
01:19:03.656 --> 01:19:04.990
alpha.

1018
01:19:05.074 --> 01:19:06.992
[reader] <i>There is not enough space.</i>

1019
01:19:07.076 --> 01:19:10.246
<i>Would you like to compress
beta or gamma?</i>

1020
01:19:10.329 --> 01:19:13.165
- Compress beta.
<i>- Beta compressed.</i>

1021
01:19:15.918 --> 01:19:17.253
Extract alpha.

1022
01:19:17.336 --> 01:19:21.799
<i>There is not enough space.
Would you like to compress gamma?</i>

1023
01:19:21.882 --> 01:19:24.718
- Compress gamma.
<i>- Gamma is compressing.</i>

1024
01:19:30.140 --> 01:19:31.183
<i>Gamma compressed.</i>

1025
01:19:43.612 --> 01:19:44.822
[Jake] Extract alpha.

1026
01:19:50.452 --> 01:19:53.455
[somber music playing]

1027
01:20:04.717 --> 01:20:06.135
[baby cries]

1028
01:20:10.514 --> 01:20:11.890
[baby coos]

1029
01:20:11.974 --> 01:20:13.225
[Yang] <i>Di-di.</i>

1030
01:20:27.865 --> 01:20:29.283
<i>Ni hao. di-di!</i>

1031
01:20:39.293 --> 01:20:41.003
<i>Di-di. wake up.</i>

1032
01:20:42.254 --> 01:20:43.672
<i>Di-di.</i>

1033
01:20:47.468 --> 01:20:49.470
<i>Is everything okay?</i>

1034
01:21:00.773 --> 01:21:02.775
[crying]

1035
01:21:25.005 --> 01:21:28.759
[Ada] <i>Hi. we're here
to help Emma Davidson.</i>

1036
01:21:28.842 --> 01:21:30.844
[Yang] <i>Yes. come in.</i>

1037
01:21:34.765 --> 01:21:36.767
[Ada] Slowly bring it down.

1038
01:21:37.768 --> 01:21:40.145
Side to side.

1039
01:21:40.229 --> 01:21:41.230
Good.

1040
01:21:46.026 --> 01:21:48.529
[Yang] Your niece is going to like me.

1041
01:21:51.198 --> 01:21:54.368
Hey. Let's go get Yang.
Come here. Go get him.

1042
01:21:54.451 --> 01:21:55.869
[laughing]

1043
01:21:58.872 --> 01:21:59.790
[laughs]

1044
01:22:03.794 --> 01:22:05.421
Can I tell you something?

1045
01:22:19.685 --> 01:22:21.061
Come on!

1046
01:22:21.145 --> 01:22:23.147
[somber music continues playing]

1047
01:23:30.130 --> 01:23:31.548
[Ada] <i>She was my great aunt.</i>

1048
01:23:32.883 --> 01:23:34.051
[Jake] <i>Your original?</i>

1049
01:23:35.260 --> 01:23:37.304
[Ada] <i>So Yang knew her?</i>

1050
01:23:37.387 --> 01:23:38.430
[Jake] <i>Yes.</i>

1051
01:23:39.806 --> 01:23:41.808
He never told you?

1052
01:23:44.686 --> 01:23:45.687
No.

1053
01:23:49.066 --> 01:23:51.485
But I always helped.

1054
01:23:56.615 --> 01:23:58.617
Sorry. [crying]

1055
01:24:03.539 --> 01:24:06.542
[gentle piano music playing]

1056
01:24:11.421 --> 01:24:14.841
I wish he would have told me
about her. Us.

1057
01:24:16.051 --> 01:24:17.052
Do you?

1058
01:24:35.487 --> 01:24:36.738
[chuckles softly]

1059
01:24:41.702 --> 01:24:43.328
He found you.

1060
01:24:46.623 --> 01:24:49.626
[gentle piano music continues playing]

1061
01:25:44.973 --> 01:25:46.224
[keypad clacking]

1062
01:25:48.602 --> 01:25:50.020
[Jake] She's asleep.

1063
01:26:23.345 --> 01:26:26.973
I don't want Yang to be
on display in the museum.

1064
01:26:29.142 --> 01:26:30.560
Neither do I.

1065
01:26:31.561 --> 01:26:32.562
But...

1066
01:26:34.439 --> 01:26:36.441
We should let them study
his memories.

1067
01:26:39.945 --> 01:26:42.572
- Do you think so?
- Yes. his existence mattered.

1068
01:26:44.491 --> 01:26:45.909
And not just to us.

1069
01:26:52.457 --> 01:26:53.458
Yeah.

1070
01:26:58.630 --> 01:26:59.881
[sighs]

1071
01:28:32.057 --> 01:28:33.433
<i>Gege.</i>

1072
01:28:34.434 --> 01:28:37.437
[speaking Mandarin]

1073
01:29:00.418 --> 01:29:02.170
[in English] Daddy.

1074
01:29:02.254 --> 01:29:03.880
Hey. what are you doing up?

1075
01:29:04.881 --> 01:29:06.299
What are you doing?

1076
01:29:08.343 --> 01:29:09.761
You want some water?

1077
01:29:11.721 --> 01:29:13.682
Want to sit beside me?

1078
01:29:13.765 --> 01:29:15.183
[footsteps approaching]

1079
01:29:20.814 --> 01:29:22.566
[Jake exhales deeply]

1080
01:29:25.068 --> 01:29:26.486
Can't sleep.

1081
01:29:27.737 --> 01:29:28.738
Me neither.

1082
01:29:31.116 --> 01:29:33.118
Don't want to say bye to <i>gege.</i>

1083
01:29:34.536 --> 01:29:35.954
Me neither.

1084
01:29:41.751 --> 01:29:45.171
[Mika. singing]
♪ <i>I want to be</i> ♪

1085
01:29:47.883 --> 01:29:51.094
♪ <i>I want to be</i> ♪

1086
01:29:53.305 --> 01:29:58.894
♪ <i>I want to be just like a melody</i> ♪

1087
01:29:58.977 --> 01:30:02.480
♪ <i>Just like a simple sound</i> ♪

1088
01:30:02.564 --> 01:30:05.984
♪ <i>Like a harmony.</i> ♪

1089
01:30:16.161 --> 01:30:19.164
["Glide" by Mitski playing]

1090
01:31:54.050 --> 01:31:57.053
[song continues]

1091
01:33:42.826 --> 01:33:44.661
[birds chirping]

1092
01:34:00.844 --> 01:34:02.846
[distant chatter]

1093
01:34:04.639 --> 01:34:05.890
[engine hums]

1094
01:34:08.560 --> 01:34:10.186
[overlapping chatter]

1095
01:34:25.910 --> 01:34:27.370
[metallic chiming]

1096
01:34:42.051 --> 01:34:43.428
[muffled thunder rumbling]

1097
01:34:52.187 --> 01:34:53.479
[water gurgling]

1098
01:35:04.365 --> 01:35:05.783
[ticking]

1099
01:35:16.878 --> 01:35:18.504
[distant singing]

1100
01:35:24.469 --> 01:35:25.553
[bird calling]

1101
01:35:26.554 --> 01:35:28.556
[metallic chiming]
